listReplacementKeys.shortDescription: This is the list of occupations to display to a respondent at the occupation question. You may include a maximum of 3 occupations.
listReplacementKeys.description: This is the list of occupations to display to a respondent at the occupation question. You may include a maximum of 3 occupations. By default your list will include Advertising / Public Relations and Marketing / Market Research and None of these.

listReplacementKeys.shortDescription: This is the list of age bands to display to a respondent at the age bands question. You need to include a minimum of 2 age bands.
listReplacementKeys.description: This is the list of age bands to display to a respondent at the age bands question. You need to include a minimum of 2 age bands.

listReplacementKeys.shortDescription: This is the list of categories to be displayed to respondents at the category usage question in the Behavioural Screener module.
listReplacementKeys.description: This is the list of categories to be displayed to respondents at the category usage question in the Behavioural Screener module. A maximum of 10 categories can be included.

listReplacementKeys.shortDescription: This is the list of categories to be displayed to respondents at the category frequency question in the Behavioural Screener module.
listReplacementKeys.description: This is the list of categories to be displayed to respondents at the category frequency question in the Behavioural Screener module. A minimum of 1 and a maximum of 6 frequency responses can be included.

listReplacementKeys.shortDescription: This is the list of categories to be displayed to respondents at the category channel purchase question in the Behavioural Screener module.
listReplacementKeys.description: This is the list of categories to be displayed to respondents at the category channel purchase question in the Behavioural Screener module. A minimum of 1 and a maximum of 6 purchase channels can be included.

listReplacementKeys.shortDescription: This is the list of social media platforms that will be displayed to respondents at the social media sharing question.
listReplacementKeys.description: This is the list of social media platforms that will be displayed to respondents at the social media sharing question. The list is preset for the fieldwork market you have selected, but you are able to add a maximum of 3 additional platforms to the list if required.

listReplacementKeys.shortDescription: This is the list of brands to be shown for the brand non rejecter and brand usage questions in the Behavioural Screener module.
listReplacementKeys.description: This is the list of brands to be shown for the brand non rejecter and brand usage questions in the Behavioural Screener module. A maximum of 18 brands can be included.

listReplacementKeys.shortDescription: This is where you upload the pack(s) to be tested.
listReplacementKeys.description: This is where you upload the pack(s) to be tested. A minimum of 3, maximum of 24 packs can be included.

listReplacementKeys.shortDescription: The Imagery Association module adds more diagnostic detail to the packs you are testing.
listReplacementKeys.description: The Imagery Association module adds more diagnostic detail to the packs you are testing. The statements can be things you want to be associated with the packs or not. There are 2 core statements included by default, but you are able to add a minimum of 1 and a maximum of 8 additional statements to the list if required.
